Text.SourceString: THE NEW FARMER!//WELCOME, WELCOME!
THERE’S A WHOLE DIFFERENT WORLD DOWN THERE. THE MORE I DIVE, THE MORE I SEE THIS ISLAND’S FULL POTENTIAL.
YOU SEE A LOT OF DEBRIS FROM THE PAST IN THE OCEAN TOO.//A BURIED STORY, IF YOU WILL.
<NPCName>JIM</> MAKES A DELICIOUS SMOKED SALMON. HE’S A BIG FAN OF SMOKED SALMON, SO YOU KNOW…//<portrait=happy>HE KNOWS WHAT MAKES IT GOOD!
I SELL SOME FISHING SUPPLIES. OH, AND WE SOMETIMES MAKE FRESH SEAFOOD MEALS.//<portrait=laugh>DON’T COUNT ON IT, THOUGH!
NO, THEY’RE VERY GOOD. IT’S JUST THAT WE DON’T ALWAYS MAKE THEM.//AND THE MENU CHANGES DEPENDING ON WHAT WE HAVE ON HAND.

THE HEALTHIER THE CORAL REEFS, THE MORE FISH THEY ATTRACT.//<portrait=happy>NOW, THAT’S JUST MY OBSERVATION… I DON’T KNOW ENOUGH ABOUT IT TO TELL YOU WHY.//<portrait=normal><NPCName>LING</> MIGHT BE ABLE TO HELP WITH THAT.
OUR LURES AND FOOD CONTAINERS ARE BIODEGRADABLE. IF THEY’RE THROWN OUT AT SEA, THEY CAN SAFELY BREAK DOWN AND RETURN TO NATURE.
IT’S IMPORTANT TO PAY ATTENTION TO OUR GARBAGE.//I’VE SEEN TOO MANY TURTLES AND OTHER ANIMALS TRAPPED IN PLASTIC.
HOW’S YOUR THURSDAY GOING SO FAR?
AH, THE BEACH… NEVER GETS OLD.//<portrait=normal>THANKFULLY, <NPCName>OLIVER</> LOVES THE BEACH AS MUCH AS HE LOVES ICE CREAM.//<portrait=happy>HE GETS THAT FROM ME.
<NPCName>JIM</> HELPS ME RUN THE SHACK. HE ALSO HELPED ME DECORATE THE INTERIOR.
HE HAS GOOD TASTE, EH?
THERE’S A WHOLE DIFFERENT WORLD DOWN THERE. THE MORE I DIVE, THE MORE I SEE THIS ISLAND’S FULL POTENTIAL.
YOU SEE A LOT OF DEBRIS FROM THE PAST IN THE OCEAN TOO.//A BURIED STORY, IF YOU WILL.

THE HEALTHIER THE CORAL REEFS, THE MORE FISH THEY ATTRACT.//<portrait=happy>NOW, THAT’S JUST MY OBSERVATION… I DON’T KNOW ENOUGH ABOUT IT TO TELL YOU WHY.//<portrait=normal><NPCName>LING</> MIGHT BE ABLE TO HELP WITH THAT.
I SELL SOME FISHING SUPPLIES. OH, AND WE SOMETIMES MAKE FRESH SEAFOOD MEALS.//<portrait=laugh>DON’T COUNT ON IT, THOUGH!
NO, THEY’RE VERY GOOD. IT’S JUST THAT WE DON’T ALWAYS MAKE THEM.//AND THE MENU CHANGES DEPENDING ON WHAT WE HAVE ON HAND.
<NPCName>JIM</> HELPS ME RUN THE SHACK. HE ALSO HELPED ME DECORATE THE INTERIOR.
HE HAS GOOD TASTE, EH?
AH, THE BEACH… NEVER GETS OLD.//<portrait=normal>THANKFULLY, <NPCName>OLIVER</> LOVES THE BEACH AS MUCH AS HE LOVES ICE CREAM.//<portrait=happy>HE GETS THAT FROM ME.
THE ISLANDS GET THEIR NAMES FROM WHAT THEY’RE FAMOUS FOR. IN OUR CASE, THE CORAL REEFS.//OTHER EXAMPLES ARE OUR NEIGHBORS, BLACK SAND ISLAND, TURTLE ISLAND, AND PUNY ISLAND, TO NAME A FEW.
I ALWAYS CHECK TO MAKE SURE TOURISTS HAVE PROPER CERTIFICATION BEFORE THEY DIVE, JUST TO BE SAFE.//THE TIDE GETS STRONG AROUND HERE, SO DIVERS NEED PROPER TRAINING.
IF YOU COLLECT FIVE OF THE SAME KIND OF KELP, YOU CAN EXTRACT THE NUTRIENTS AND USE THEM TO UPGRADE THE QUALITY OF YOUR SEEDS, ANIMAL FEED, AND ALL THAT SORT.
THE LAB CAN HELP WITH THAT…//<portrait=normal>IT’S RIGHT ACROSS FROM THE COMMUNITY CENTER.
WE MAKE BAIT AND LURES OURSELVES.//WHEN WE HAVE EXTRA TIME, WE MIGHT DO OTHER THINGS LIKE SMOKE SOME SALMON.
SMOKE OTHER FISH? HMM… I DON’T KNOW IF WE’D DO THAT, ACTUALLY.//<portrait=happy><NPCName>JIM</> IS IN CHARGE.

IF YOU COLLECT FIVE – OR TEN OR SOMETHING LIKE THAT – OF THE SAME KIND OF KELP, YOU CAN EXTRACT THE NUTRIENTS.//AND YOU CAN USE THEM TO UPGRADE THE QUALITY OF YOUR SEEDS, ANIMAL FEED, AND ALL THAT SORT.
THE LAB CAN HELP WITH THAT…//<portrait=normal>IT’S RIGHT ACROSS FROM THE COMMUNITY CENTER.
THE ISLANDS GET THEIR NAMES FROM WHAT THEY’RE FAMOUS FOR. IN OUR CASE, THE CORAL REEFS.//OTHER EXAMPLES ARE OUR NEIGHBORS, BLACK SAND ISLAND, TURTLE ISLAND, AND PUNY ISLAND, TO NAME A FEW.
I ALWAYS CHECK TO MAKE SURE TOURISTS HAVE PROPER CERTIFICATION BEFORE THEY DIVE, JUST TO BE SAFE.//THE TIDE GETS STRONG AROUND HERE, SO DIVERS NEED PROPER TRAINING.
YOU CAN DIVE VERY DEEP IN THE OCEAN. UP TO FORTY METERS, I THINK.//YOU MIGHT NEED TO CLEAR THE AREA FIRST TO FIND THE WAY DOWN.
OH, YOU KNOW WHAT I’M TALKING ABOUT.//CLEARING THE TRASH ON THE OCEAN FLOOR AND ALL THAT.
THE SHACK IS DOING ALL RIGHT TODAY.//WE HAVE LOYAL CUSTOMERS, THANKFULLY.
<NPCName>JIM’S</> CHILDREN ARE MUCH OLDER THAN <NPCName>OLIVER</>. I’D SAY <NPCName>THEO</> IS ABOUT YOUR AGE.
AND I THINK <NPCName>THEO</> IS SINGLE, IF YOU’RE CURIOUS. HEH HEH… BUT DON’T QUOTE ME ON THAT.
SURE, YOU CAN FISH WITHOUT BAIT, BUT YOUR CHANCES ARE BETTER IF YOU USE IT.
WE MAKE IT IN BATCHES AT THE SHACK… JUST FOR YOUR INFORMATION.
<NPCName>JIM’S</> CHILDREN ARE MUCH OLDER THAN <NPCName>OLIVER</>. I’D SAY <NPCName>THEO</> IS ABOUT YOUR AGE.
AND I THINK <NPCName>THEO</> IS SINGLE, IF YOU’RE CURIOUS. HEH HEH… BUT DON’T QUOTE ME ON THAT.
I STILL FISH HERE AND THERE.//A GOOD ACTIVITY. BUT I DON’T DO IT AS OFTEN AS I USED TO.
OLD AGE, I GUESS. HEH HEH.
SURE, YOU CAN FISH WITHOUT BAIT, BUT YOUR CHANCES ARE BETTER IF YOU USE IT.
WE MAKE IT IN BATCHES AT THE SHACK… JUST FOR YOUR INFORMATION.
IMAGINE HAVING FOUR CHILDREN LIKE <NPCName>BETTY</>. WHAT A FUN HOUSEHOLD IT MUST BE… WELL, FOR ME ANYWAY. I ALWAYS LIKE A BIG FAMILY.
YOU’RE RIGHT. IT ISN’T FOR EVERYBODY. YOU KNOW WHAT IS? FISHING.
I’M TEACHING <NPCName>OLIVER</> TO KEEP HIS HEAD DOWN. YOU KNOW, BE HUMBLE… EVEN IF IT’S ABOUT SOMETHING HE’S GOOD AT.
A LITTLE HUMILITY CAN’T HURT. THINKING THERE’S ALWAYS ROOM FOR IMPROVEMENT CAN ONLY DRIVE US TO LEARN MORE. BESIDES, EVERYONE HAS SOMETHING TO TEACH, RIGHT?
I’M TEACHING <NPCName>OLIVER</> TO KEEP HIS HEAD DOWN. YOU KNOW, BE HUMBLE… EVEN IF IT’S ABOUT SOMETHING HE’S GOOD AT.
A LITTLE HUMILITY CAN’T HURT. THINKING THERE’S ALWAYS ROOM FOR IMPROVEMENT CAN ONLY DRIVE US TO LEARN MORE. BESIDES, EVERYONE HAS SOMETHING TO TEACH, RIGHT?
IT MAKES ME SAD TO THINK ABOUT ALL THE OIL SPILLS THAT WOULD HAPPEN IF PUFFERFISH GOES THROUGH WITH THEIR DRILLING PLANS.
I HOPE THEY RETHINK THEIR DECISION.
I’M STOCKING UP ON SHIITAKE BEFORE SPRING ENDS.
I DON’T THINK THERE’LL BE ANY MUSHROOMS DURING SUMMER…//<portrait=sad>WELL, NOT AROUND HERE, AT LEAST.
HAPPY SUMMER! IT’S THE PERFECT WEATHER TO PUT ON YOUR WET SUIT AND DIVE IN, <PlayerName>$PLAYER</>.
EXPLORE WHAT’S DOWN THERE. AREN’T YOU CURIOUS?
DEBRIS FROM OLD SHIPWRECKS DRIFTS IN EVERY ONCE IN A WHILE.
THE TRASH FROM THE WRECKS IS ONE THING, BUT I GET CURIOUS. YOU GOTTA WONDER WHAT HAPPENED TO THE SHIPS.
I WENT TO THE WOODLAND THE OTHER DAY TO TAKE <NPCName>OLIVER</> TO SCHOOL.//AND THEN I FORAGED FOR SOME WILD FRUIT. FOUND SOME WATERCRESS INSTEAD. HMM…
AND STILL NO MUSHROOMS. *sighs*
I’M EXCITED FOR FALL. I CAN FINALLY GATHER SOME MUSHROOMS AND ROAST THEM.
I’VE BEEN CRAVING ROASTED MUSHROOMS ALL WEEK.
I’LL BE JOINING THE BEACH CLEANUP ON THE 27TH. I NEVER MISS A CHANCE TO SEE ALL MY FRIENDS.
I HOPE TO SEE YOU THERE TOO, <PlayerName>$PLAYER</>. I’LL BE SUPPLYING THE COCONUT DRINK FOR EVERYBODY TO REHYDRATE.
OH, FOR TOMORROW? YEAH, YOU DON’T NEED TO BRING ANYTHING. JUST GET A LOT OF SLEEP TONIGHT SO YOU HAVE ENERGY TOMORROW MORNING.//THE TOWN COMMISSIONED US TO SUPPLY THE MEALS AND DRINKS FOR EVERYONE.
BLACK TRUMPET MUSHROOMS ARE SPROUTING ON THE ISLAND. MUSIC TO MY EARS!
I FOUND PLENTY OF MUSHROOMS BY THE LAKE THE OTHER DAY.//HAVE YOU FOUND ANY?
I FOUND A FEW CHESTNUTS THE OTHER DAY, BUT I HAVEN’T MADE ANYTHING WITH THEM.
I SUPPOSE I COULD JUST ROAST THEM AND CALL IT A DAY. HMM…
CAN YOU FEEL THE COLD WIND? I THINK IT’S GOING TO SNOW SOON.
THE SHACK SEEMS TO SELL MORE FISH IN SUMMER… I THINK PEOPLE JUST GRILL MORE WHEN THE SUN. IS OUT.
WILL YOU BE GOING TO THE HARVEST FESTIVAL, <PlayerName>$PLAYER</>?
<NPCName>JIM</> AND I WILL HAVE A FISHING BOOTH. HOPEFULLY, OUR DISPLAY WILL MAKE MORE PEOPLE INTERESTED IN WHAT WE DO.
PET DAY IS ALWAYS A BLAST. EVERYONE IS OUT ENJOYING THE NICE WEATHER, SOCIALIZING, AND BEING WITH ANIMALS.
ON THE FLIP SIDE, IT’S PROBABLY THE RIGHT TIME TO GET YOUR WINTER COAT READY FOR THE SNOW.
WE’RE TURNING THE HEATER ON EVERY DAY NOW. NOT AT NIGHT, THOUGH.//WE ALWAYS TURN IT OFF BEFORE BED.
I CAN’T WEAR A JACKET THAT’S TOO THICK.//IT GETS IN THE WAY OF WALKING IF IT’S TOO HEAVY OR BULKY.
RUNNING OUT OF THINGS TO DO, EH, <PlayerName>$PLAYER</>?
WHY NOT MAKE USE OF THE SEASON TO IMPROVE YOUR FISHING SKILLS?
SOME FLOWERS SURVIVE WINTER. LIKE PANSIES AND ALL THAT SORT.//IF YOU’RE INTERESTED, THERE ARE A LOT OF SPOTS NEAR THE OLD LIGHTHOUSE THAT MIGHT HAVE SOME. CHECK OVER THERE.
I DON’T THINK THERE ARE ANY MUSHROOMS YET, UNLESS I’M GRAVELY MISTAKEN.
THE WINTER FAIR KEPT US UP A BIT LATER THAN WE USUALLY PREFER.
IT WAS A BIT LOUD AT NIGHT. BUT IT’S ALL GOOD.
THERE ARE DIFFERENT TYPES OF FISH IN WINTER THAN THE ONES YOU CATCH DURING SUMMER.
YOU NEVER KNOW WHAT’S REALLY OUT THERE UNTIL YOU ENCOUNTER IT.
IT’S NICE AND SUNNY TODAY…//<portrait=laugh>HA! FEELS WEIRD TO SAY MY NAME OUT LOUD.
I DON’T MIND A LITTLE BIT OF BREEZE AND ALL THAT SORT.
I TRY TO TAKE <NPCName>OLIVER</> TO SCHOOL ON RAINY DAYS. MAKE SURE HE DOESN’T SLIP AND ALL THAT.
I’M TRYING TO STAY INDOORS AS MUCH AS I CAN.// JUST DON’T LIKE THE RAIN THAT MUCH.
I DECIDED TO TAKE THE DAY OFF AND HAVE A NICE HOT CUP OF TEA.
ARE YOU TRYING TO KEEP WARM TOO? I DON’T BLAME YOU.//<portrait=concerned>I’M WEARING THIS, AND I’M STILL COLD.
I DON’T KNOW ALL OF THEM, BUT THERE ARE FISH THAT ONLY COME OUT DURING THE RAIN.
THERE ARE ALSO FISH THAT PREFER TO SWIM IN THE EVENING. KEEP THAT IN MIND, <PlayerName>$PLAYER</>.
SOMETHING SOUPY MIGHT DO TONIGHT.
I’LL JUST MAKE A POT, AND I CAN EAT SOME TOMORROW TOO.
I TRY TO TAKE <NPCName>OLIVER</> TO SCHOOL ON RAINY DAYS. MAKE SURE HE DOESN’T SLIP AND ALL THAT.
I’M TRYING TO STAY INDOORS AS MUCH AS I CAN.// JUST DON’T LIKE THE RAIN THAT MUCH.
I DECIDED TO TAKE THE DAY OFF AND HAVE A NICE HOT CUP OF TEA.
ARE YOU TRYING TO KEEP WARM TOO? I DON’T BLAME YOU.//<portrait=concerned>I’M WEARING THIS, AND I’M STILL COLD.
LOOK AT THIS STORM. IT’S WORRISOME.
THE WIND WAS SO LOUD LAST NIGHT. IT WOKE ME UP, AND I USUALLY SLEEP LIKE A LOG.//<portrait=concerned>THANKFULLY, IT DIDN’T WAKE <NPCName>OLIVER</> UP.
SOMETHING SOUPY MIGHT DO TONIGHT.
I’LL JUST MAKE A POT, AND I CAN EAT SOME TOMORROW TOO.
I PUT ON MY LEG WARMERS THIS MORNING WHEN I SAW IT WAS SNOWING.
OF COURSE, THEY HELP WITH THE COLD.
WE RARELY GET VISITORS FROM THAT PART OF THE ISLAND. TOO FAR TO WALK, I THINK…
I UNDERSTAND. MY KNEES AREN’T EXACTLY SHINY AND NEW THESE DAYS.
DON’T STOMP TOO HARD, WILL YOU? THERE’S DUST FALLING OVER HERE.
SURE, TAKE A SEAT WHEREVER YOU’D LIKE. FEEL FREE TO STAY AS LONG AS YOU PLEASE!
I KEEP PICTURES OF SOME OF MY PROUDEST CATCHES IN MY LIVING ROOM, IF YOU WANT TO CHECK THEM OUT.
THERE ARE A COUPLE OF NEWS ARTICLES ABOUT THEM AS WELL.//<portrait=normal>I DON’T USUALLY CARE ABOUT STUFF LIKE THAT, BUT FISH, I CARE ABOUT.
<NPCName>JIM</> IS BACK IN THE KITCHEN…
OY, <NPCName>JIM</>! STILL THERE? <PlayerName>$PLAYER</> IS HERE!
IT WAS MY WIFE, <NPCName>ELEANOR</>, WHO DECORATED THIS SHACK. THE HOUSE PART OF THE SHACK, ANYWAY…//<portrait=happy><NPCName>JIM</> WAS THE ONE WHO DID THE SHOP DECORATING.
<NPCName>ELEANOR</> SURE IS SPECIAL, ISN’T SHE?
I HATE DECORATING ANYWAY.
IT’S A NICE CHANGE TO RELAX HERE ONCE IN A WHILE.
FOR ONE, IT’S A CHANGE OF SCENERY.//<portrait=laugh><NPCName>FRANK</> HERE IS DEFINITELY A SIGHT FOR SORE EYES. HEAR THAT, <NPCName>FRANK</>?!
THE FOOD HERE IS PRETTY GOOD. BUT THE PASTRY ISN’T <NPCName>BETTY’S</>. STILL GOOD, THOUGH…//<portrait=happy>BUT HIS MOM MAKES MEAN PASTRIES.
HEY, NO OFFENSE, <NPCName>FRANK</>!
PHEW! WHAT A WALK. MY KNEES WEREN’T BUILT TO GO SO FAR SO FAST.
OH, YOU’RE HERE EARLY.
AHEM… THE LOT OVER THERE IS A PRETTY GOOD SPOT IF YOU WANT TO FIND FLOWERS.
ARE YOU HUNTING FOR MUSHROOMS?
ARE YOU HUNTING FOR SHALLOTS?
PHEW! WHAT A WALK. MY KNEES WEREN’T BUILT TO GO SO FAR SO FAST.
ENJOYING THE SUMMER WEATHER SO FAR?
IT’S NICE TO CATCH A BIT OF SUN OUT HERE BEFORE IT SETS.
I ALWAYS REMEMBER TO WEAR MY WINDBREAKER WHEN I COME HERE. PRACTICAL, SURE.
IT HOLDS A LOT OF FISHING GEAR, BUT IT ALSO KEEPS ME WARM.
I KEEP PICTURES OF SOME OF MY PROUDEST CATCHES IN MY LIVING ROOM, IF YOU WANT TO CHECK THEM OUT.
THERE ARE A COUPLE OF NEWS ARTICLES ABOUT THEM AS WELL.//<portrait=normal>I DON’T USUALLY CARE ABOUT STUFF LIKE THAT, BUT FISH, I CARE ABOUT.
YOU CAN ALWAYS TELL WHEN THE BIG FISH ARE OUT. THERE’S A CERTAIN SMELL COMING FROM THE WATER.
MAYBE IT’S JUST THE SMELL OF A THOUSAND FISH, THOUGH.
HOW’S LIFE ON THE FARM?
I REMEMBER SITTING IN THE SUN FOR HOURS WHEN I USED TO FISH.//SOMETIMES I’D JUMP IN THE WATER JUST SO I COULD COOL OFF, AND I’D SCARE AWAY ALL THE FISH.
YOU OUGHT TO DO SOMETHING FUN TODAY, <PlayerName>$PLAYER</>! LIKE THE KIDS SAY, YOU HAVE TO TREAT YOURSELF!
I KNOW <NPCName>OLLIE</> SEEMS LIKE A QUIET KID, BUT HE GETS SO EXCITED WHEN HIS FAVORITE SHOW COMES ON TV.//IT’S ABOUT A BOY DETECTIVE WHO SOLVES MYSTERIES.
I DON’T PRETEND TO UNDERSTAND ALL OF IT, BUT I TRY TO WATCH IT WITH HIM AT LEAST A FEW TIMES A WEEK.//IF HE DIDN’T HAVE TO GO TO SCHOOL, I THINK THAT’S ALL HE’D DO ALL DAY.
I THINK I’LL DO SOMETHING DIFFERENT AFTER WORK TODAY. MAYBE I’LL TAKE A WALK AROUND THE LAKE OR SAY HELLO TO SOME FOLKS IN TOWN. SOUNDS LIKE A FUN TIME TO ME!
YOU CAN ALWAYS TELL WHEN THE BIG FISH ARE OUT. THERE’S A CERTAIN SMELL COMING FROM THE WATER.
MAYBE IT’S JUST THE SMELL OF A THOUSAND FISH, THOUGH.
I KNOW THIS PLACE LOOKS A LITTLE ROUGH AROUND THE EDGES, BUT THAT’S THE WAY I LIKE IT.//IT’S THE BEACH SHACK, AFTER ALL, NOT THE BEACH MANSION.
HEH HEH. BEACH MANSION…//<portrait=normal>OH, COME ON! THAT WAS FUNNY.
THE BREEZE FEELS WONDERFUL TODAY. MAYBE I SHOULD TAKE A WALK ON THE BEACH.
<NPCName>JIM</> BEAT ME AT CHESS LAST NIGHT.//I THOUGHT I HAD IT IN THE BAG, BUT HE PULLED OUT A SURPRISE WIN AT THE LAST MOMENT.
GUESS I’D BETTER START PRACTICING AGAIN!
<NPCName>OLIVER’S</> BEEN SAYING HE WANTS TO BE A POLICE DETECTIVE WHEN HE GROWS UP.
I KNOW HE CAN DO ANYTHING HE PUTS HIS MIND TO, SO HE’S GOT MY SUPPORT THE WHOLE WAY.
I’M CRAVING ROASTED MUSHROOMS TODAY, FOR SOME REASON. MAYBE I’LL MAKE SOME FOR DINNER.
<NPCName>OLLIE’S</> NOT A BIG FAN OF THEM, SO WE’LL HAVE TO MAKE SOMETHING DIFFERENT FOR HIM.
FEEL FREE TO BRING ME ANY FISH YOU CATCH. I’D BE HAPPY TO SIZE THEM UP!
IT’S GETTING WARMER AND WARMER EVERY DAY!
I’VE BEEN THINKING ABOUT WHAT I SHOULD GET FOR <NPCName>OLLIE’S</> BIRTHDAY.//HE REALLY WANTS A NEW HAT, BUT I SAW A NEW BOY DETECTIVE SHIRT HE MIGHT LIKE.
MAYBE I’LL JUST GET HIM BOTH. WHAT’S WRONG WITH A LITTLE SPOILING EVERY NOW AND THEN?
I’VE LIVED ON CORAL ISLAND MY WHOLE LIFE, BUT SEEING THE TREES AND FLOWERS BLOOM EACH YEAR STILL DAZZLES ME.
WE’RE LUCKY TO LIVE IN SUCH A BEAUTIFUL WORLD.
<PlayerName>$PLAYER</>! YOU’VE TURNED INTO A TOMATO WITH ALL THE TIME YOU’VE SPENT OUTSIDE.
WHY GROW TOMATOES WHEN YOU CAN JUST BECOME ONE YOURSELF?
<NPCName>OLLIE</> ALWAYS GETS ME SOMETHING SMALL FOR MY BIRTHDAY. HE’S SUCH A GOOD KID.
I CAN’T BELIEVE SUMMER’S ALREADY OVER. IT GOES BY FASTER AND FASTER EVERY YEAR.
IF YOU HURRY, YOU MIGHT BE ABLE TO GET IN ONE MORE SWIM BEFORE THE WATER GETS TOO COLD.
HAVE YOU SEEN THE FOREST THIS SEASON?//IT’S BEAUTIFUL! THE TREES LOOK LIKE THEY’RE ON FIRE.
WALKING ALONG THE WATER THIS TIME OF YEAR IS HARD.//THE OCEAN KEEPS NIPPING AT YOUR TOES, AND THE WATER IS FREEZING.
IT’S STILL FUN, THOUGH!
’TIS THE SEASON! IT ALWAYS FEELS LIKE THE WHOLE WORLD IS CELEBRATING IN WINTER.
YOU OUGHT TO TAKE IT EASY THIS WINTER, <PlayerName>$PLAYER</>. YOU’VE BEEN WORKING HARD ALL YEAR.
<NPCName>OLLIE</> LOVES TO BUILD SNOWMEN. THIS YEAR, HE WANTS TO MAKE ONE IN THE SHAPE OF BOY DETECTIVE.//I TOLD HIM HE SHOULD MAKE IT ON THE BEACH SO ALL THE FISH CAN SEE IT.
THERE’S NOTHING WRONG WITH A LITTLE RAIN HERE AND THERE. IT CERTAINLY COOLS YOU OFF.
RAINY DAYS WERE ALWAYS EVENTS WHEN I WAS YOUNGER.//WE’D HAVE TO HAUL THE BOAT INSIDE THE SHACK SO IT DIDN’T GET RUSTY.
YOU KNOW WHAT? I DON’T KNOW. HEH HEH.//BUT IT SEEMED TO WORK.

Special.SourceString: Is that right? Seawater won’t rust a boat, but rain will?

Text.SourceString: HEH HEH! THANKS.//IT SEEMED LIKE A GOOD IDEA AT THE TIME.

Special.SourceString: That sounds like a lot of work. You’re very diligent!

Text.SourceString: TRY FISHING TODAY, <PlayerName>$PLAYER</>! YOU NEVER KNOW WHAT YOU’LL CATCH ON A RAINY DAY.
A DAY LIKE THIS IS PERFECT FOR A NICE LONG ROUND OF CHESS.
<NPCName>OLLIE</> ALWAYS SLEEPS WELL ON RAINY NIGHTS. THE SOUND REALLY CALMS HIM.
IT CALMS ME TOO!
I HOPE THIS RAIN CLEARS UP BY TOMORROW. <NPCName>OLIVER</> REALLY WANTED TO GO SURFING.
EVEN IF IT’S WARM OUTSIDE, RAINY DAYS MAKE ME CRAVE TEA AND HOT SOUP.
I WAS GOING TO MAKE SOMETHING DIFFERENT FOR DINNER TONIGHT, BUT MAYBE I SHOULD JUST GO FOR SOUP INSTEAD.
THE SEA IS ALWAYS ANGRY ON DAYS LIKE THIS. EVEN I WOULDN’T RISK FISHING WHEN THE WATER’S THAT CHOPPY.
I KNOW I SHOULDN’T BE OUT WHEN THE WEATHER’S LIKE THIS, BUT BEING OUT IN A STORM ALWAYS MAKES ME FEEL SO FREE.
YOU LOOK A LITTLE WATERLOGGED, <PlayerName>$PLAYER</>! GO HOME AND DRY OFF.
WE’VE GOT QUITE THE RAGING STORM OUTSIDE. ARE YOU SURE YOU CAN MAKE IT HOME IN THIS WEATHER?
FEEL FREE TO CAMP OUT IN THE SHACK IF YOU NEED TO. IT’S A LITTLE SANDY, BUT IT’S BETTER THAN BEING WET.
<PlayerName>$PLAYER</>! YOU LOOK LIKE YOU’VE SEEN A GHOST. IS THE STORM REALLY THAT BAD?
SNOW! I’D ALMOST FORGOTTEN WHAT IT FEELS LIKE. NOW I REMEMBER. WET, COLD, BLUSTERY…
SNOW IS A LOT MORE MAGICAL WHEN YOU’RE A KID.
IF THE SNOW KEEPS PILING UP LIKE THIS, I’LL HAVE TO SHOVEL A PATH TO THE SHACK DOOR.
MAYBE <NPCName>OLIVER</> CAN HELP.
YOU CAN’T BE WARM IN THAT GETUP, <PlayerName>$PLAYER</>. HEAD HOME AND WARM YOURSELF UP IN FRONT OF A FIRE!
YOU KNOW WINTER HAS REACHED CORAL ISLAND WHEN IT STARTS SNOWING.
ON DAYS LIKE THIS, I USED TO MAKE SURE THE BOAT WASN’T FROZEN. IT HAPPENS MORE OFTEN THAN YOU’D THINK.
HOPEFULLY, WE WON’T BE STUCK IN THE SHACK UNTIL THE SNOW STOPS TOMORROW! I’LL HAVE TO DIG EVERYTHING OUT AGAIN.
[<NPCName>Sunny</> seems busy behind the counter.]
WHAT’S UP, <PlayerName>$PLAYER</>? I CAN SPARE A MOMENT.
NOTHING IMPORTANT? NO PROBLEM.//<portrait=laugh>SEE YOU LATER!
SOMETIMES I THINK I SHOULD CALL THIS PLACE THE SAND SHACK.//WE GET BURIED A LITTLE MORE EVERY DAY.
WHAT AM I WATCHING? OH, IT’S NOTHING IMPORTANT.//I JUST LIKE TO HAVE SOMETHING ON IN THE BACKGROUND WHILE I DOZE.
THIS IS THE ONLY TIME I GET TO WATCH THE NEWS.//AS SOON AS <NPCName>OLLIE</> COMES IN, HE’LL WANT TO CHANGE THE CHANNEL TO BOY DETECTIVE.
I DON’T MIND, BUT IT WOULD BE NICE TO DO SOMETHING DIFFERENT FOR A CHANGE.
IT’S BEEN A LONG DAY. I DIDN’T THINK WE’D HAVE SO MANY CUSTOMERS TODAY.
EVERYONE’S ALWAYS KIND, BUT STANDING ON MY FEET ALL DAY REALLY DOES A NUMBER ON MY BACK… THEN AGAIN, MAYBE THAT’S FROM ALL THE YEARS I SPENT HUNCHED OVER A FISHING ROD.
THE SEA. WHAT A MAJESTIC THING.
[<NPCName>Sunny</> is staring out over the water.]
DO YOU THINK THERE ARE FISH OUT THERE WE HAVEN’T DISCOVERED YET?//THERE MUST BE HUNDREDS OR EVEN THOUSANDS OF SPECIES WE DON’T KNOW ABOUT.
THIS ISLAND NEEDS PEOPLE WHO CARE ABOUT CORAL REEFS. NOT JUST RESTORING THEM, BUT ALSO NURTURING AND PROTECTING THEM.//IF YOU PAY ATTENTION TO THE NEWS, YOU KNOW CORAL REEFS ARE THREATENED WORLDWIDE.
TRASH AND POLLUTION CAN BE VERY DAMAGING TO CORAL REEFS.//IT CAN MAKE THEM SICK… YES, CORAL REEFS CAN GET SICK.
NOW, DON’T FORGET TO MENTION IT TO <NPCNAME>FRANK</>, OKAY?//TELL HIM YOU’VE HAD BETTER SEAFOOD AT THE SHACK. HA HA.
TEASE HIM FOR ME, WILL YA?//A COMPETITIVE ONE, THAT BOY.
CORAL REEFS ARE A MAJOR ECOSYSTEM FOR FISH, SEA MAMMALS, AND MANY OTHER SEA CREATURES.//KIND OF LIKE A HOUSE FOR THEM…
WE MUST ACCEPT THE FACT THAT WE’RE NOT ALONE IN THIS WORLD.//<PORTRAIT=HAPPY>OTHER THINGS LIVE IN IT. WE HAVE A RESPONSIBILITY TO TAKE CARE OF OUR NEIGHBORS’ ENVIRONMENT TOO.
<NPCNAME>OLIVER</> SWIMS LIKE A FISH. HE’S EITHER SWIMMING OR SURFING.//THAT KID IS NEVER OUT OF THE WATER.
IT’S GOOD, THOUGH. IT’S GOOD TO HAVE HOBBIES.
MY HAIR GROWS SO FAST. I HAVE TO GET IT CUT EVERY OTHER WEEK.//OR ELSE IT’LL GROW AND GROW.
I DON’T LIKE LONG HAIR. IT FEELS VERY ITCHY, ESPECIALLY RIGHT NOW IN THE SUMMER HEAT.
THANKFULLY, THE WAVES HAVE NEVER GOTTEN SO HIGH THAT WE HAD TO MOVE.//I’VE BEEN HERE FOR A LONG TIME, AND WE’RE DOING JUST FINE.
I DON’T THINK I’D KNOW WHERE TO GO IF WE HAD TO MOVE AWAY FROM THE BEACH.//<portrait=happy>I WOULDN’T PARTICULARLY LIKE TO LIVE IN THE WOODLAND AREA … SO, MAYBE NEAR THE LAKE.
OH, I HAVE TO PICK UP SOME FLOUR FOR THE KITCHEN FROM SAM’S.//HUMPH… I DON’T FEEL LIKE GOING.
MAYBE I CAN JUST ASK <NPCNAME>JIM</> TO PICK UP GROCERIES ON HIS WAY IN TOMORROW.
IF <NPCNAME>OLIVER</> EVER DECIDES TO MOVE OFF THE ISLAND ONE DAY, AND HE WANTS US TO GO WITH HIM, WE’LL GLADLY DO IT.
THERE ISN’T MUCH HOLDING US HERE… SURE, <NPCNAME>ELEANOR</> AND I WOULD MISS THE SHACK, BUT <NPCNAME>OLIVER</> IS OUR PRIORITY.
